parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive brake pedal travel can lead to delayed or insufficient braking, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when towing or in emergency stopping situations.
symptoms: The brake pedal travels excessively before the brakes engage
requiring the driver to apply excessive pressure or almost stand on the brake pedal to stop the vehicle
especially when towing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The prolonged stopping distance can increase the risk of accidents, especially in emergency stopping situations.
symptoms: The vehicle takes a long time to stop
even when the brake pedal is pushed hard as possible.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front brakes can lead to a loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The front brakes fail to function properly
resulting in a loss of stopping power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear wheel hub assembly can cause the wheel to come off while driving, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injury or death.
symptoms: Strange handling
vibration
or noise from the rear of the vehicle
wheel comes off while driving
brake drum separation
damage to surrounding components such as fenders
lug nut studs
and wheels.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The wobbling of the steering column can cause the vehicle to be difficult to steer and control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially on the highway.
symptoms: The steering column wobbles
the steering wheel shakes or vibrates
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the vehicle is hard to control through traffic and on the highway.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Loose or Faulty Steering Column Adjustment
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A loose or faulty steering column adjustment can cause the steering column to wobble, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering column wobbles
the steering wheel shakes or vibrates
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the vehicle is hard to control through traffic and on the highway.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An engine compartment fire can cause significant damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to a loss of control, accidents, and injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Smoke or flames visible from the engine compartment
burning smell or odor
engine overheating
engine stalling or loss of power
warning lights or alarms on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the right side seat track can cause the seat to become unstable, potentially leading to loss of control of the vehicle, accidents, or injuries to occupants.
symptoms: The right side seat track is broken
the seat is unstable or loose
the seat does not stay in place
the seat moves unexpectedly while driving
the seat is difficult to adjust.
